headline.print_headline: Va. Governor Vows to Expand Medicaid on His Own
headline.main: Va. Governor Vows to Expand Medicaid on His Own

lead_paragraph: Democratic Gov. Terry McAuliffe vowed Friday to bypass the General Assembly and expand Medicaid eligibility for about 400,000 low-income residents on his own, a move Republican lawmakers immediately promised to fight.
